{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"10921f76-2476-462b-8ac0-d862e053b517","content":"On macOS, the OS automatically captures crash reports — no `createdump` needed. Here's where to look:\n\n**Crash Reports (`.ips` / `.crash` files):**\n```\n~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/\n/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/\n```\nLook for files matching your process name. You can also open **Console.app → Crash Reports** to browse them.\n\n**Core Dumps (optional, disabled by default):**\n```bash\n# Enable core dumps for future runs\nulimit -c unlimited\n```\nCores are written to `/cores/`. Note that SIP may prevent core dump generation on some macOS versions.\n\n**Quick find:**\n```bash\n# Find recent crash reports for your app\nls -lt ~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/ | head\n```\n\nThe `.ips` crash report includes the faulting thread, stack trace, and signal info — usually enough to diagnose NativeAOT crashes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9f7d7936-c129-4f1e-8362-e5d5c0467089","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about finding crash dumps/reports for a NativeAOT .NET application on macOS, without `createdump`. This is a general knowledge question — no tools needed.\n\nOn macOS, when an app crashes, the system automatically generates crash reports. Here's the key info:\n\n1. **macOS Crash Reports** are stored in `~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/` (for user apps) or `/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/` (for system-wide).\n2. You can also use **Console.app** to view them.\n3. The files have extensions like `.crash` or `.ips`.\n\n\n4. For core dumps specifically, macOS disables them by default — you'd need to enable them with `ulimit -c unlimited`, and they'd be written to `/cores/`. Since `createdump` is a CoreCLR tool and doesn't ship with NativeAOT apps, you're relying entirely on the OS-level crash reporting mechanisms.","outputTokens":478,"requestId":"980F:3387D:5415DC0:5CA6498:69F40683"},"id":"e1f31f9c-5ff9-47a8-8cb6-6d5542f8d865","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:49:03.234Z","parentId":"1c90a2a0-1284-463e-bcd4-bb8aaa2713af"}
